            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reboil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong>, <strong>diced carrot </strong>and <strong>bay leaf[ves]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Combine your <strong>beef stock mix </strong>and <strong>red wine paste </strong>with 250ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [325ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>red wine stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-7-1688140471004-x200.jpg",
