          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-7-1688140475354-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the potatoes to a low heat with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a splash of <strong>milk</strong>, season with a pinch of <strong>pepper </strong>and mash until smooth</p><p>Once the duck has had an initial 25 min, pour the <strong>pie filling</strong> into the dish with the duck and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Top with the <strong>mashed potato</strong>, <strong>grated cheese </strong>and <strong>remaining chopped thyme</strong> and put the dish in the oven for 15-20 min or until golden brown and bubbling – this is your<strong> shredded duck leg pie</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
